arts.ttl: Leeds United and Daniel Farke handed vital double title race boost following Derby County win
arts.sum: Both Rodon, who opened the scoring against Derby, and Wilfried Gnonto, who came on as a substitute, went into the game on four yellow cards. Gnonto also avoided a yellow card, meaning that both, fitness permitting, will be available for the midweek clash.

arts.ttl: Max Wober opens up on Leeds United 'relief' after Elland Road struggles
arts.sum: On opening his United goal-scoring account, Wober told Sky Sports: "It was a really good feeling. "It was important for us to go into half-time with a two-goal lead.

arts.ttl: Daniel Farke press conference LIVE as Leeds United boss reacts to table-topping Derby County win
arts.sum: Follow everything the manager has to say about Saturday afternoon's match below as we bring you most of the questions and answers in full from the debrief. Isaac Schmidt also returned, while Junior Firpo was fit enough to start at left-back.

arts.ttl: Paul Warne makes frank Derby County admission after 'uncomfortable' Leeds United defeat
arts.sum: The Rams were beaten 2-0 as Daniel Farke's side moved top of the Championship with goals from £10m defender Joe Rodon and a strike from Max Wober settling the game before half-time. Paul Warne admitted he was not surprised by Leeds United win over Derby County and admitted there was "gulf in class" between the clubs.

arts.ttl: 3 key passes, 94% success: It’s about time this Leeds United ace got the credit he deserves
arts.sum: While it’s never a shock to see Ao Tanaka is helping run the show for Leeds in midfield, his partner Rothwell was the man of the moment on Saturday afternoon. Leeds United cruised to a 2-0 home victory over Derby County on Saturday, more of the same from the Whites in a dominant home display.

arts.ttl: Paul Warne left frustrated as Derby County boss highlights key moment in Leeds United defeat
arts.sum: Disappointed boss Paul Warne was left cursing Derby County's defending for Leeds United's opening goal as the Rams fell to a 2-0 defeat at Elland Road. It was disappointing to concede from a set piece because I didn't think we were getting cut open.

arts.ttl: Daniel Farke provides big Leeds United injury update after 'dominant' Derby County win
arts.sum: First half goals from Joe Rodon and Max Wober, who replaced Firpo at left-back, ensured the Whites returned to winning ways and moved back to the top of the Championship. Leeds United boss Daniel Farke has confirmed Junior Firpo picked up a hamstring injury during their home win over Derby County.

arts.ttl: Derby County player ratings v Leeds United as gulf in quality clear but trio stand out
arts.sum: Derby County saw Leeds United move to the top of the Championship as goals from Joe Rodon and Max Wober secured a 2-0 win at Elland Road. Derby tried to get to half-time without conceding a second but that proved beyond them when a Brenden Aaronson cross nicked off Jerry Yates allowing Wober to score from close range.

arts.ttl: Leeds brush aside Derby to go top of Championship
arts.sum: The hosts struck twice late in the first half.

arts.ttl: Leeds United player ratings as Rodon, Wober and Tanaka impress in Derby victory
arts.sum: There was still time after that for Wober to break his own duck and squeeze in at the back post for a tap-in after great work by Daniel James and Brenden Aaronson. Rodon headed home a maiden Whites goal from a Joe Rothwell corner.
